    {
      "paragraph_name": "PASFLPCB",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This copybook defines the structure of the PASFLPCB, which is likely a Program Communication Block (PCB) used within an IMS (Information Management System) environment for database interactions. The PCB provides a communication interface between the application program and the IMS database. It contains various fields that describe the database, segment, and processing options. PASFL-DBDNAME (line 18) specifies the database name associated with this PCB. PASFL-SEG-LEVEL (line 19) indicates the segment level. PASFL-PCB-STATUS (line 20) provides the status of the PCB after an operation. PASFL-PCB-PROCOPT (line 21) defines the processing options for database access. PASFL-SEG-NAME (line 23) holds the name of the segment being accessed. PASFL-KEYFB-NAME (line 24) and PASFL-NUM-SENSEGS (line 25) are related to key feedback and the number of sensitive segments, respectively. PASFL-KEYFB (line 26) contains the key feedback information, which is the fully concatenated key of the last accessed segment. This copybook is included in programs that need to interact with an IMS database through this PCB.",
